abstract: Ending years of uncertainty, the Dutch defense ministry said the country would replace its fleet of F-16 jets with F-35s made by Lockheed Martin but would buy fewer than planned.
snippet: Ending years of uncertainty, the Dutch defense ministry said the country would replace its fleet of F-16 jets with F-35s made by Lockheed Martin but would buy fewer than planned.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — The Dutch defense ministry said on Tuesday that it had selected the F-35 fighter jet from Lockheed Martin to replace its aging fleet of F-16s, bringing an end to years of uncertainty over the Netherlands’ commitment to a program that has been plagued by technical delays and mounting development costs.

headline.main: Dutch Pick F-35 Jets to Expand Aging Fleet
headline.print_headline: Dutch Pick F-35 Jets To Expand Aging Fleet
